a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"rel\";s:9:\"alternate\";s:4:\"type\";s:9:\"text/html\";s:4:\"href\";s:98:\"http://design.tutsplus.com/articles/new-course-mastering-perspective-in-adobe-photoshop--cms-22996\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:5:\"en-US\";}}s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"New Course: Mastering Perspective in Adobe Photoshop\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:5:\"en-US\";}}s:7:\"content\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2478:\"<p>Our new design course,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://design.tutsplus.com/courses/mastering-perspective-in-adobe-photoshop?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost&amp;utm_content=CRS-200141&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost_CRS-200141\" target=\"_self\">Mastering Perspective in Adobe Photoshop</a>,&nbsp;will help you to learn, practice, and apply the lessons of setting scenes in perspective using Adobe Photoshop.&nbsp;</p><h2>What You\'ll Learn</h2><p>Tuts+ instructor&nbsp;<a href=\"https://tutsplus.com/authors/kirk-nelson?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost&amp;utm_content=CRS-200141&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost_CRS-200141\" target=\"_self\">Kirk Nelson</a>&nbsp;will take you through&nbsp;three different types of perspective scenes: one, two, and three-point perspective.&nbsp;You will learn how to recognize each type of perspective system, and develop scenes of your own to match.</p><p>The chapters follow along with that breakdown and use the general rhythm of Learn, Practice, Apply. So each chapter will contain its own project of setting up a scene in perspective and compositing a new element into the scene to match.&nbsp;<br></p><p>By the end of this course you’ll be comfortable working in&nbsp;one, two, and three-point perspective to create beautiful, realistic scenes.&nbsp;</p><h2>Watch the Introduction<br></h2><p><iframe src=\"//fast.wistia.net/embed/iframe/c08wrmmeqz\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" class=\"wistia_embed\" name=\"wistia_embed\"></iframe></p><h2>Start Learning for Just $15</h2><p>You can take our new course straight away by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://tutsplus.com/pricing?utm_source=Tuts+&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=teaserpost&amp;utm_content=CRS-200141&amp;WT.mc_id=Tuts+_referral_teaserpost_CRS-200141\" target=\"_self\">subscribing to Tuts+</a>. For just $15 a month, you get access to this course and hundreds of others, with new ones added every week.<br></p><div class=\"mediafed_ad\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://audio.tutsplus.com.feedsportal.com/c/35227/f/668805/s/22996/sc/4/mf.gif\" width=\"1\" /><a href=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/186529796139/u/407/f/668805/c/35227/s/22996/a2.htm\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/186529796139/u/407/f/668805/c/35227/s/22996/a2.img\" /></a><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/186529796139/u/407/f/668805/c/35227/s/22996/a2t.img\" width=\"1\" /></div>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"html\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:5:\"en-US\";}}s:9:\"published\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"2015-01-08T18:18:35.000Z\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:5:\"en-US\";}}s:7:\"updated\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"2015-01-08T18:18:35.000Z\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:5:\"en-US\";}}s:6:\"author\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"\n      \n    \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:5:\"en-US\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"name\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrew Blackman\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_