INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES (2,1,'2014-09-11 06:14:03','2014-09-11 06:14:03','<h3><span style=\"color: #339966;\">PROJECT PARTNERS</span></h3>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #339966;\">Implementing Partners:</span></h4>\r\nCSEED works in partnership with local authorities, technical specialists and  local branches of mass organizations at different levels for the implementation of development projects. These implementation project partners are shown in the table below:\r\n<br/>\r\n<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/image2.png\" alt=\"partners\" />\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #339966;\">Financial Partners:</span></h4>\r\nThe projects managed and technically supported by CSEED are financed by International Development agencies. In addition to this financial support, these partners have provided technical advice and carried out monitoring which contributes to the success of projects and ensures optimum impact with the targeted beneficiary communities. Our financial partners include:\r\nAgency of International Cooperation for Development (AECID) - Spain\r\nConemund - Spain\r\nEntraide ét Fraternité\r\nEuropean Commission\r\nMisereor - Germany\r\nWallonie Bruxelles International (WBI) - Belgium\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #339966;\">Cooperation and Networks:</span></h4>\r\nCSEED has established and maintained good relations and cooperation with other Vietnamese NGOs, Research Institutes and Universities to make best use of technical services  and collaborating jointly in implementing projects effectively. Joint initiatives include working with: Research and Training Centre for Community Development - RTCCD, Handicraft Research and Promotion Centre - HRPC, Rural Development Service Centre - RDSC, National Institute of Sociology -  IOS, Water Resource Institute -  WRSI.\r\n\r\nCSEED participates in a range of networks and forums of International and Vietnamese NGO\'s, UN and Embassy networks and forums to exchange, share development experiences and advocacy for more strategic support for poor and vulnerable communities. The working groups with CSEED participation are: Ethnic Minorities Working Group - EMWG, Gender and Community Development Network - GenComNet, Climate Change - CC, Community Participation Network  -  Comparnet.','Partnership','','publish','closed','open','','sample-page','','','2014-11-18 03:05:39','2014-11-18 03:05:39','',0,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2011-07-30 15:38:18','2011-07-30 15:38:18','<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/image4_1.jpg\" alt=\"img4\" width=\"500px\" />\r\n\r\nDuring 26 and 28 December 2008, the handing over ceremony of irrigation and clean-water constructions between CSEED and Huu Lung District People\'s Committee, Lang Son province was organised under the project VC006 funded by Manos Unidas (Spain). \r\n\r\nThe irrigation and clean-water constructions including two irrigation schemes of O O and Ho Rung Chua  and two clean-water system were completed which improve the accessibility to drinking and irrigation water for the villagers here. Specially, 1,317 people of Dong Sinh, Dong Ma, Da Mai and Tan Hop villages - Tan Lap commune have got benefits from the upgraded irrigation schemes as they have their paddy fields within the irrigated area and 252 people of Lan Mo and Lan Vau villages have received the supports from the project for households-scale water tanks to store clean water for daily use as these two villages are suffering from lack of clean water as the water resources from forest mountain become less.\r\n\r\nThe villagers here are very happy to receive the water and they are all committed to strictly follow the regulations of water use and project maintainance. As estimated, spring crop for rice will be got 40 ha more in O O system and 25ha more in Ho Rung Chua; winter crop for rice will be got 45 ha more in O O system and 25 ha more in Ho Rung Chua system for maize, soybean, potato, vegetables... Rice yields increased from 4 tons/ha - 4.2 tons/ha for summer crop 3.5 tons/ha - 3.8 tons/ha for spring crop. Estimated a total net income generated is around VND 694,175,000 per year equivalent to USD 43,659.     ','Handing-over ceremony of irrigation and clean-water constructions between CSEED and Huu Lung District - Lang Son province','','publish','closed','open','','pellentesque-habitant-morbi-tristique-senectus','','','2014-11-07 09:54:12','2014-11-07 09:54:12','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=4',0,'post','',0),(5,1,'2012-07-30 15:37:44','2012-07-30 15:37:44','','5709944739_578bc434a7_b','','inherit','open','open','','5709944739_578bc434a7_b','','','2012-07-30 15:37:44','2012-07-30 15:37:44','',0,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/5709944739_578bc434a7_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(7,1,'2011-07-30 15:45:43','2011-07-30 15:45:43','<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/02banner.jpg.jpg\" alt=\"img7\" width=\"600px\"/>\r\n\r\nYesterday, Sunday 15 February 2009, in vestige Van Mieu - Quoc Tu Giam, CSEED held-up an Exhibition on Giấy Dó (Handmade paper) under the CSEED project VC004 funded by Cordaid - Neitherlands. \r\n\r\nAttending the exhibition, the visitors had served with cơm-lam (bamboo-tube rice) and witnessed the processes of handmade paper production and products from Giấy Dó such as envelops, greeting cards, album, calendar,… . \r\n\r\nThe Muong ethnic minority group in Suoi Co village, Hop Hoa commune, Luong Son district, Hoa Binh province is the target group of this project component. They lived on agriculture production before, but now their incomes and living conditions have been improved thanks party to handmade paper production. CSEED\'s VC004 project has supported\r\nthe Suoi Co group with the provision of several initial facilities and equipment, co-operated with HRPC in technical training, material reservation as well as business and management capacity building. \r\n\r\nThe CSEED model of Giấy Dó production has made both social and economic impacts. It initially brought abouteconomic benefit for the group, with each member household having increased their monthly income by VND 500,000 (equivalent to USD 30) . Moreover, the use of this model has contributed to the preservation of some of the indigenous knowledge of the Vietnamese people, and has made a small contribution to the cause of poverty reduction in the country. ','CSEED holds a Giấy Dó (Handmade paper)Exhibition','','publish','closed','open','','elit-eget-tincidunt-condimentum-eros-ipsum-rutrum-orci','','','2014-11-07 08:56:42','2014-11-07 08:56:42','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=7',0,'post','',0),(8,1,'2012-07-30 15:45:09','2012-07-30 15:45:09','','1945802905_691d175718_b','','inherit','open','open','','1945802905_691d175718_b','','','2012-07-30 15:45:09','2012-07-30 15:45:09','',0,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/1945802905_691d175718_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(11,1,'2010-07-30 15:58:05','2010-07-30 15:58:05','<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/muchu.jpg\" alt=\"muchu\" />\r\n\r\nThe couple of Ms. Nguyen Thi Mieu 43 year old and Mr. Nguyen Van Vi 33 year old has two children living in Ngam village, Tien Son commune, Luong Son district, Hoa Binh province. The oldest daughter is pupil of 9th and the youngest son is pupil of 4th. Before getting married, Mieu studied at 4th class and Mr. Vi finished learning at 2nd class. This situation is common in Luong Son at that time. After getting married, the couple was very busy to work for feeding children. They have no time to read newspaper, magazines, or books and rarely watching TV due to lost of electricity happen very often here. Year by year, Vi has forgotten what he learned in the school and his wife has just remembered a little. “Peasants don’t need to study”, they thought. However, it is not true. Two children are growing and then they went to school. Now, they have a lot home work to ask parents for doing but their parents could not help them. Day by day, they did not share any thing to parents because they thought parents could not read so off course parent did not understand any things especially in modern life now. But Mieu and Vi were so worried. Children grow up but they still are small girl and boy.  Parents need to learn many things to talk and share with children and teach them how to take care themselves in the life. Last year, CSEED help village to open one class of erasing illiteracy. Vi wanted to attend but was reluctant. Because the class has a lot women. Mieu asked her husband why delaying to take part in class. When she knew, she decided to go class together with husband. Two children also encourage parent going to class together. They promised to take care cooking and other work at home. So their parents did not worry any more when studying in the class.  It was glad because the class has more two couple learning together like Mieu and Vi. All of them feel happy to study together. The class helps them to read, to write and to calculate…Now both parents and children are sharing many things very often and arranging working better.  Last month, the class ended. Vi and Mieu and other people expect that CSEED will open more classes like this one then they have more chance to learn more.','Erasing illiteracy is really helpful for us','','publish','closed','open','','consectetur-adipisicing-elit','','','2014-11-18 04:04:16','2014-11-18 04:04:16','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=11',0,'post','',0),(12,1,'2012-07-30 15:57:23','2012-07-30 15:57:23','','OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA','','inherit','open','open','','olympus-digital-camera','','','2012-07-30 15:57:23','2012-07-30 15:57:23','',0,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/4756831209_cfe3227937_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(14,1,'2010-07-30 15:59:32','2010-07-30 15:59:32','The family of Ms. Ma Thi Yen who is 45 years old has 5 people, her couple and her 3 children. Her family is ranked by the villagers to be one of the poorest in Na Rien village.\r\n \r\nThere is nothing worthy in her house: only a small wooden house, a small radio for information. When they want to watch television, they have to get their neighbours’ houses. Now, their life is much better than 3-4 years before. They do not have to suffer from hunger; rice or maize cultivated is enough for household consumption. However, they still have many difficulties, the income of the household only depends on 5 sao of filed and a little land for maize cultivation. When they need to expense or pay school-fee for their children, they have to sell paddy or chicken and ducks for money. In Na Rien village, they can only cultivate 1 crop per year as there is not enough water for 2 crops.  In some well-off households, they can afford to buy or hire water-pump so that they can cultivate more than us. I can not afford to hire or buy water pump, I can only plant maize or tobacco in 1 sao. If our village can be supported with an irrigation system, our life will be improved so much.\r\n \r\nSome months ago, the village leader informed that the project implemetned by CSEED approved to support dam building in Na Rien and various activities like establishing farmers interest groups (sow raising, bee-keeping,…). On hearing those, all of the villagers in my village had a meeting with Mr Cuong – a district staff, some members at the commune and villge to select the members for village development committee. We also registered to attend project activities. My family registered into sow-raising group as I found that this activity would help my family to increase our income, and the market of sow is sustainable as there are only 1-2 sows and piglets in the whole village brought from Thai Nguyen, so the price is too high. I find that all the people in my village are very eager to register into different farmers interest groups like bee-keeping or sow-raising as these needs were raised by ourselved to the district staff and CSEED for project preparation and implementation planning in the village.\r\n \r\nSince we were informed about the new project, I have seen that the members of VDC, the leader of sow-raising group shared that they were being trained varous skills by the project, after that they will conduct training for us. My husband also attended the village meeting discussing about the plan to build Na Rieng dam at the end of this year. In general, I found that CSEED project is very suitable and appropriate to our expectations. I hope that we will receive much more supports from the project.','Story of Ms. Ma Thi Yen, Tay minority group in Na Rien village, Yen Cu commune, Cho Moi district, Bac Kan province','','publish','closed','open','','maecenas-mattis-tortor-ut-posuere-aliquam','','','2014-11-18 04:02:20','2014-11-18 04:02:20','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=14',0,'post','',0),(15,1,'2012-07-30 15:59:14','2012-07-30 15:59:14','','4088743235_690996beef_o','','inherit','open','open','','4088743235_690996beef_o','','','2012-07-30 15:59:14','2012-07-30 15:59:14','',14,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/4088743235_690996beef_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(17,1,'2010-07-30 16:01:43','2010-07-30 16:01:43','CSEED’s new project for Lang Son province: VC008\r\n \r\nAn Agreement for project VC008 was signed by CSEED and People’s Committee of Van Quan district on 6 March 2008.\r\n \r\nFunded by CORDAID (a Dutch NGO) with the total budget of 3,455,991,000 vnd for 3 years, in which local will contribute 746,036,000 vnd in kinds, VC008 was designed to improve health status for women in the disadvantaged communities of Van Quan district, Lang Son province.\r\n \r\nAccording to this project design, 228 mobile bathrooms, 228 animal cages of ethnic people (moving their animal cages beneath their stilted houses out to a hygienic place) will be built and necessary tolls for HIV/AIDS infection provention (soap) will be provided. It is supposed that all 14,293 women from the age of 15-49 in all 24 communes and town of Van Quan district will gain better awareness of common health issues and receive better healthcares from the district health system; and all the heath workers at district, commune and village levels will get benefit from trainings/workshops on professional, management, monitoring, communication,… and the facilitation skills as well as supports to consolidate the whole district health system for more efficient operations and better services provision. Not only the above beneficiaries, this project also bring indirect benefit to local authorities, including district and commune offices/bodies in terms of experience in project management and organisation of development activities for their locality as well as the participatory approaches in working with the communities; and mass-organistions such as Women Union, Youth Union,… who involve in life-cares of the local communities will also get benefits from the project, i.e. experiences in integrating healthcare activities into social and productions activities and skills in community mobilization, communications,…\r\n','CSEED’s new project for Lang Son province: VC008','','publish','closed','open','','morbi-in-sem-quis-dui-placerat','','','2014-11-18 03:59:55','2014-11-18 03:59:55','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=17',0,'post','',2),(19,1,'2012-07-30 16:01:01','2012-07-30 16:01:01','','5495738902_4258a1965c_b','','inherit','open','open','','5495738902_4258a1965c_b','','','2012-07-30 16:01:01','2012-07-30 16:01:01','',17,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/5495738902_4258a1965c_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(21,1,'2012-07-30 16:04:09','2012-07-30 16:04:09','On 29 April 2009, the closing workshop of VC004 project Community Asset Improvement for Livelihoods of Poor Communities was held in Luong Son People’s Committee.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/02banner.jpg.jpg\" alt=\"img21\" width=\"500px\"/>\r\n\r\nMore than sixty participants attented the workshop were CSEED Director and Project Officer, Project Management Board and Working Team, representatives of project related Departments of Luong Son district and beneficiaries. After the speech summarily reported all project activities, the participants actively contributed their opinions to the project, both on successes and obstacles/limitations. The project were highly appreciated with good impacts to increase the households’ income through loan, breeding animals, contribute to improve the villagers’ health, enthusiasm of stakeholders, good performance of project management board members,…\r\n\r\nMr. Ly Kim Huong, Dao ethnic monirity, Ngoc Lam village, Cao Ram commune, said: “We had no concept of gender equality until the project comes to training. We, the men often took rests after working on the field, just gathered and talked together, we ignored the women’s voice as we thought that women knew nothing. But, since CIDSE/CSEED training on gender equality, men in our village has helped their wives much more, and discuss with the wives in any issues”.\r\n\r\nMoreover, literacy training was one of the most expected activities to the people here. Inspite of the rain, the coldness, the busyness, they still go to class with a torch every evening.\r\n\r\nBesides, there were still some limitations such as some project activities have not met the villagers’ needs like few literacy classes, project supported training on animal raising and provided with breedings but lack of veterinary training. The lessons-learnt were consolidated for a better performance in the future\r\n\r\nThe local authorities and Vulunteer Village Development Committee in each village were committed to continue managing and implementing the project activities. They also assigned the responsibilities to each stakeholders clearly and drew the mechanism of project managing and reporting.\r\n\r\nAll the project stakeholders, especially the beneficiaries, expected that the project will continue following phases. In which, handmade paper production still needs more supports.\r\n\r\nThis is considered one of the most sucessful CSEED’s projects.','Closing Workshop of VC004 project in Luong Son District – Hoa Binh  Province','','publish','closed','open','','praesent-adipiscing-mi-eget-ipsum-imperdiet-elementum','','','2014-11-07 08:52:07','2014-11-07 08:52:07','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=21',0,'post','',0),(22,1,'2012-07-30 16:03:41','2012-07-30 16:03:41','','3844115347_1fef316b6a_b','','inherit','open','open','','3844115347_1fef316b6a_b','','','2012-07-30 16:03:41','2012-07-30 16:03:41','',21,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/3844115347_1fef316b6a_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(24,1,'2012-07-30 16:07:28','2012-07-30 16:07:28','Ngày 1 tháng 2 năm 2010, lễ ký kết thỏa thuận dự án mới giữa Trung tâm CSEED và Huyện Lạc Sơn - tỉnh Hòa Bình được tổ chức long trọng tại Ủy Ban Nhân Dân huyện Lạc Sơn - tỉnh Hòa Bình.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/image24_1.jpg\" alt=\"image24_1\" width=\"600px\" />\r\n\r\nThe project “Effective land use and diversified environmental livelihoods for poor communities, Lac Son District, Hoa Binh  Province” (Project Code: VC010) is the second project that CSEED implemented in Lac Son District after the project – “Community Empowerment for Improved Living Standards – VC001” ends (2005 – 2007). This project is supported by Entraide et Fraternite (E&F) and Wallonie Bruxelles International (WBI). \r\n\r\n<br/>\r\n[one_half]\r\nThe new project will be implemented in 2010 untill December 2011 with the purposes that improving the households economy through promoting an effective land use  and diversified environmental livelihoods in six villages of the three communes in Lac Son District, Hoa Binh Province. This project will bring direct benefits to 3,481 people in 665  poor households, mainly Muong ethnic minority. The project strategies are capacity building for villagers, Community Based Organisations (CBOs), project partners at commune and district on  development issues and approach; supporting appropriate small scale irrigation system for one village and capacity building relating to land use for farmers; supporting technical and credit to villagers for agriculture production and non farm activities and internalising cross-cutting aspects for villagers and local authority by involving them in the project process and facilitate them to work as development practioners and advocators.\r\n[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]\r\n<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/image24_2.jpg\" alt=\"img24_2\" />\r\n[/one_half_last]','AGREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN HOA BINHPROVINCE –  VC010','','publish','closed','open','','lorem-ipsum-dolor-sit-amet','','','2014-11-18 03:51:25','2014-11-18 03:51:25','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=24',0,'post','',0),(26,1,'2012-07-30 16:06:17','2012-07-30 16:06:17','','3266055425_eed1ecc779_b','','inherit','open','open','','3266055425_eed1ecc779_b','','','2012-07-30 16:06:17','2012-07-30 16:06:17','',0,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/3266055425_eed1ecc779_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(30,1,'2012-07-30 16:09:49','2012-07-30 16:09:49','[one_half]<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1266.jpg\" alt=\"image30_1\" width=\"300px\" />[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]\r\nKhuoi Deng I and II villages are two villages of Tan Son commune, Cho Moi district,Bac Kan province having natural bamboo area up to 180 ha.\r\nThese bamboo resources have partially contributed to villager’s income here. However, the local bamboo was just sold as raw products such as cutting tree and binding them to sell at low price.\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\nUnder Cho Moi Integrated Community Development Project, In August 2009, CSEED in collaboration with Xuan Lai traditional bamboo processing co-operative organized basic and advanced training courses and exposure visit for villagers of these two villages to production site of Xuan Lai co-operative. A set of bamboo processing machine was also provided to the two villages. After receiving the above-mentioned supports, villagers were able to do preliminary processing i.e. they know how to make the tree from curve\r\nto straight and to make the most of the tree; therefore 30% material was saved. This contributed to sustain bamboo for future usage.In addition, the products are very aesthetic, eye-catched and it can adapt household’s needs such as table, chair, tea tray, fishing-rod, farmer’s pipe...\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Cay-mot-danh.jpg\" alt=\"img30_2\" width=\"600px\"/>\r\n\r\nMoreover, Xuan Lai traditional bamboo processing co-operative also expressed their demand to buy the big quantity of preliminarily processed bamboo with about two times higher price than current price. Some villagers and dealers also expressed their interests in buying these products at 3-5 times higher price than selling raw materials.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn conclusion, those support is a good start which enable villagers in two villages identify their valuable local resources and have good plan for using these resources for their development.. In the coming time, CSEED will support to enable them to work as bamboo processing group and to follow environmental friendly manner systematically. Thus, we hope this activity can contribute to bring effects and sustainability in socio-economic developments for households in these two villages.','Effects from CSEED support to bamboo furniture processing in  Cho Moi Integrated Community Development Project','','publish','closed','open','','legere-urbanitas-nam-an-nusquam-intellegam','','','2014-11-07 04:43:09','2014-11-07 04:43:09','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=30',0,'post','',0),(31,1,'2012-07-30 16:09:30','2012-07-30 16:09:30','','423659645_11bb162aef_o','','inherit','open','open','','423659645_11bb162aef_o','','','2012-07-30 16:09:30','2012-07-30 16:09:30','',30,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/423659645_11bb162aef_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(33,1,'2012-07-30 16:12:08','2012-07-30 16:12:08','On 05th of April 2013, Tan Son District People\'s Committee (DPC), Phu Tho province and Centre for Community Socio-Economic and Environmental Development – CSEED signed agreement for project \"Improving quality of life for rural poor\".\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_0720.jpg\" alt=\"meeting\" width=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis project is finaned by European Union in Vietnam and Entraide et Fraternite in Belgium. The project will be implemented in Thu Cuc and Vinh Tien commune, Tan Son district, Phu Tho province. Project duration is 3 years from March 2013 to February 2016. Project specific objective is to imoprove income, living condition and quality of life of poor ethinic minority families and their participation in development process.\r\n\r\nTo achieve above mentioned objective, project will support to address main constraints suffered by villagers in 4 surveyed villages, ie. food shortage, poor living condition, insufficient service, inadequate inclusion of poor ethnic minority communities and discrimination against women. Strategies to address these constraints are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Capacity building for local authorities, technical staff at district and commune level and\r\ncommunity-based organisation so that they can support communities implementing the action\r\neffectively and manage development process beyond this project;</li>\r\n	<li>Capacity building for villagers on participatory planning, participation in decision making, technical\r\nproduction and bussiness for current crops/animal raising and piloting new crops to improve\r\nincome and food security.</li>\r\n	<li>Provision of in-kind support and construction of irrigation system for improving agriculture\r\nproduction</li>\r\n	<li>Extending irrigation system into drinking water system by installing purifying system and\r\ncombining the technical training for environment friendly livelihoods extending its content into\r\nhygiene environment education for improved living condition of the villagers;</li>\r\n	<li>Advocating to local authority for improved extension and veterinary service system, effective\r\ninclusion of poor ethnic minority communities and of hard-to-reach villages in development\r\nprocess which will provide opportunities to poor ethnic minority people to take part in all forms of\r\nparticipation including participating in planning, implementing, benefiting and decision making.</li>\r\n</ul>','GREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN TAN SON DISTRICT, PHU  THO PROVINCE – (Project code: VC017)','','publish','closed','open','','cu-vel-suas-interpretaris-no-qui-tantas','','','2014-11-07 04:28:55','2014-11-07 04:28:55','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=33',0,'post','',0),(34,1,'2012-07-30 16:11:16','2012-07-30 16:11:16','','7543602860_c741e700c0_b','','inherit','open','open','','7543602860_c741e700c0_b','','','2012-07-30 16:11:16','2012-07-30 16:11:16','',33,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/7543602860_c741e700c0_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(36,1,'2012-07-30 16:14:22','2012-07-30 16:14:22','Dear colleagues and friends,\r\n \r\nNon-farm is one of the activities supporting the disadvantaged and vulnerable communities to improve \r\ntheir livelihoods. As a result of this support, CSEED organises an exhibition on Giay Do (handmade \r\npaper) production performed by the villagers in Suoi Co village, Hop Hoa commune, Hoa Binh province - \r\none of CSEED VC004 project beneficiaries.\r\n \r\nTime: 9am - 5 pm, Sunday 15 February 2009\r\nVenue: Van Mieu - Quoc Tu Giam, Hanoi\r\n \r\nCSEED would like to invite you to this event.\r\n \r\nCSEED hopes to receive your support and attendance to this event as your encouragement to the \r\ndisavantaged and vulnerable communities. \r\n \r\nPlease download the letter of invitation and the agend','Invitation to CSEED Handmade Paper Exhibition','','publish','closed','open','','at-ferri-officiis-reprehendunt-mea','','','2014-11-07 08:57:57','2014-11-07 08:57:57','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=36',0,'post','',0),(37,1,'2012-07-30 16:14:04','2012-07-30 16:14:04','','3461164183_544861afff_b','','inherit','open','open','','3461164183_544861afff_b','','','2012-07-30 16:14:04','2012-07-30 16:14:04','',36,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/3461164183_544861afff_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(39,1,'2012-07-30 16:19:22','2012-07-30 16:19:22','<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Cay-mot-danh.jpg\" alt=\"img39\" width=\"600px\" />\r\n\r\nThis afternoon, 22 April 2009, the Project Agreement Signing Ceremory was held at Van Quan District People\'s Committee between CSEED and Van Quan District - Lang Son province.\r\n\r\nWith the support by Caritas Switzerland, the three-year project on Disadvantaged peasants diversify their livelihoods (code VC009) starting in 2009 aims to enhance the living conditions for the poor farmer households by promoting their assets to improve their diversified livelihoods, contributing to sustainability of natural resource utilization and natural environment protection. This project will bring direct benefits to 1,342 people in 275 households, mainly Nung ethnic minority in five villages of the two poorest communes in Van Quan: Phu My and Viet Yen and target in livelihoods and environmental protection with cross-cutting issues like gender equality, community-based organnisation capacity building.','NEW PROJECT AGREEMENT SIGNED FOR LANG SON PROVINCE','','publish','closed','open','','elementum-mauris-aliquam-ut-ac-nam-eu','','','2014-11-07 08:54:29','2014-11-07 08:54:29','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=39',0,'post','',0),(40,1,'2012-07-30 16:19:13','2012-07-30 16:19:13','','7650666944_0ca214439e_b','','inherit','open','open','','7650666944_0ca214439e_b','','','2012-07-30 16:19:13','2012-07-30 16:19:13','',39,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/7650666944_0ca214439e_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(42,1,'2012-07-30 16:23:20','2012-07-30 16:23:20','<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Picture-002.jpg\" alt=\"img42_1\" />\r\nTo strengthen the Community Based Organisations’ capacity, CSEED conducted a technical training on legal isues and economic contract development and signing in Cho Moi People’s Committee, BacKan province during 10-12 June 2009. under the project VC005 which is supported by CaritasAustralia. \r\n \r\nParticipants in this training were twenty-two VC005’s project partners (of which 9 women catched 40.9%) including representative of Project Management Board and accountant at district level and CBOs’ leaders ie. Farmer Interested Groups (FIGs) leaders, accountants and cashiers from Village Development Commitees from 7 project villages. Ms.Tran Thi Hoa Binh - Doctor in Laws, Director of Legal Support and Consulting Centre (under National Economics University) was invited to facilitate this training. \r\n \r\nThe training cource was highly appreciated. Most of the participants who had never got acquainted to legal concepts and issues did understand their interests and obligations in contract implementation. They could compose a contract in accordance with Vietnamese laws and, one of the most successes of this training was that, they could find inadequation points in any contract to negotiate through contract assessment skills they were provided. ','VC005 conducts training on legal isues and economic contract development and signing','','publish','closed','open','','tempor-nisl-vel-non-id-at-cumque-nibh','','','2014-11-07 08:47:31','2014-11-07 08:47:31','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=42',0,'post','',1),(43,1,'2012-07-30 16:23:03','2012-07-30 16:23:03','','4704140020_7122011014_b','','inherit','open','open','','4704140020_7122011014_b','','','2012-07-30 16:23:03','2012-07-30 16:23:03','',42,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/4704140020_7122011014_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(45,1,'2012-07-30 16:30:02','2012-07-30 16:30:02','On 12 January 2011, the Project Agreement Signing Ceremony was held formally at Thai Thuy District People\'s Committee between CSEED and Thai Thuy District – Thai Binh Province.\r\n\r\n\r\n[one_half]<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1107.jpg\" alt=\"image45_1\" width=\"300px\"/>[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1113.jpg\" alt=\"img45_2\" width= \"300px\" />[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\n\r\nThe project “Diversified livelihoods and improved resilience of the vulnerable coastal communities toward climate change adaptation in Thai Thuy District, Thai Binh Province” (Project Code: VC011) is supported by Misereor and will be implemented from October 2010 until September 2013.\r\n\r\nThe main purpose of this project is to reduce vulnerability of the coastal communities in five villages of Thai Do and Thai Thuong communes through diversifying their livelihoods and building up their resilience towards climate change adaptation in sustainable manner. The project is expected to bring direct benefits to 5,048 people belong to 1,206 households of 5 villages in Thai Do and Thai Thuong communes, Thai Thuy District, Thai Binh Province. Most of project beneficiaries will be farmers engaging in agriculture and aquaculture production and pupils who have suffered and will climate change and environment issues in the coming years. The poor will be prioritized because of their low response capacity and high vulnerability to the climate changes. The project will focus on some following main matters:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Diversifying the sustainable aquaculture;</li>\r\n	<li>Developing the good model of sustainable productions adapting with climate change and meeting the food security</li>\r\n	<li>Improving the community’s capacity on climate change preventation</li>\r\n</ul>','AGREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN THAI BINH PROVINCE – VC011','','publish','closed','open','','maecenas-mattis-tortor-ut-posuere-aliquam-2','','','2014-11-07 04:38:19','2014-11-07 04:38:19','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=45',0,'post','',2),(46,1,'2012-07-30 16:29:46','2012-07-30 16:29:46','','7015157331_4ff9f7772a_b','','inherit','open','open','','7015157331_4ff9f7772a_b','','','2012-07-30 16:29:46','2012-07-30 16:29:46','',45,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/7015157331_4ff9f7772a_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(48,1,'2012-07-30 16:34:54','2012-07-30 16:34:54','On 09th of February 2012, Tan Son District People\'s Committee (DPC), Phu Tho province and Centre for Community Socio-Economic and Environmental Development – CSEED signed  agreement for project \"Sustainable agro-forestry development and marketing of ecological products from poor rural families in Tan Son - Tan Son District, Phu Tho Province\r\n\r\nThe project is co-financed by Spanish Agency for International Development Cooperation - AECID and a Spanish NGO - CONEMUND. The project will be implemented in four poor villages of Dong Son and My Thuan communes, Tan Son district, Phu Tho province.\r\n\r\nAccording the project agreement, the project will be implemented within 2-year time with the aim to improve food security through improved agricultural and forestry livelihoods for poor people in four villages of two communes in Tan Son district, Phu Tho province.\r\n\r\nSpeaking at the signing ceremony, Mr Bui Van Huan, Vice Chair of Tan Son District People’s Committee, Chairman of Project Management Board said that this project in  a poor district of Tan Son is not only a great opportunity to improve people\'s lives through the development of sustainable livelihoods, but it also helps improving capacity of officials at various levels in implementing project activities and using new skills in performing their organisations’ mandates. Tan Son District People’s Committee will assign relevant and committed staff to implement project effectively.','AGREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN TAN SON DISTRICT, PHU THO PROVINCE– VC015','','publish','closed','open','','cu-vel-suas-interpretaris-no-qui-tantas-2','','','2014-11-18 03:44:14','2014-11-18 03:44:14','',0,'http://themes.tielabs.com/365news/?p=48',0,'post','',3),(49,1,'2012-07-30 16:34:36','2012-07-30 16:34:36','','6813233319_752a42a794_b','','inherit','open','open','','6813233319_752a42a794_b','','','2012-07-30 16:34:36','2012-07-30 16:34:36','',48,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/6813233319_752a42a794_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(102,1,'2012-07-31 14:38:40','2012-07-31 14:38:40','<h2>Toggles Blocks</h2>\r\n[toggle title=\"Your Title 1\" state=\"open\" ]suscipit sed at montes at tellus. Aliquam nisl penatibus commodo massa mi rutrum, ut massa mollis dolor dui at, tortor ullamcorper vel diam pretium sit leo, pellentesque in leo eu mauris mollis aliquam, ultricies adipiscing eu a dui sollicitudin posuere. Massa vivamus ac ipsum, pede enim quam sit, mus aliquam amet pede quis laboriosam.[/toggle]\r\n<code>[toggle title=\"Your Title 1\" state=\"open\"]some text[/toggle]</code>\r\n\r\n[toggle title=\"Your Title 2\" state=\"close\" ] [dropcap]S[/dropcap]uscipit sed at montes at tellus. Aliquam nisl penatibus commodo massa mi rutrum, u