an style=\"color: #008000;\">WHO WE ARE</span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Centre for Community Socio-economic and Environmental Development (CSEED) is a\r\nVietnamese Non - Governmental Organization (NGO), which was established by the Vietnam\r\nUnion of Science and Technology Associations (VUSTA) under Decision No 77/QD-LHH dated 17\r\nJanuary 2006. CSEED was formed by the staff of Community Development Department of CIDSE\r\nVietnam - an International NGO - as a part of the planned empowerment and management role\r\nhand-over to a local NGO after CIDSE\'s 27 years of working in Vietnam.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">CSEED staff who had worked with International NGOs have good knowledge and skills in\r\nmanaging programme. Our professional expertise in economics, agriculture, sociology and\r\nenvironment are relevant to the organization\'s programme focus.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Our Vision</span></h4>\r\nVulnerable and marginalized communities are empowered within equitable society and achieve\r\nsustainable livelihoods and environmental development.\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Our Mission</span></h4>\r\nCSEED enables vulnerable and marginalized communities to achieve sustainable livelihoods and\r\nenvironmental development through:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Supporting communities and partner organisations to initiate and manage livelihoods and\r\nenvironmental development programmes</li>\r\n	<li>Strengthening capacities of communities and farmers’ groups and their access to resources</li>\r\n	<li>Piloting innovative development initiatives and conducting action research</li>\r\n	<li>Advocating on livelihoods and environmental policies and implementation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Our Values[lightbox full=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_0720.jpg\" title=\"Mission\"][/lightbox]</span></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ownership</li>\r\n	<li>Partnership</li>\r\n	<li>Equity</li>\r\n	<li>Transparency and Accountability</li>\r\n	<li>Efficiency</li>\r\n	<li>Sustainability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Target Groups</span></h4>\r\nCSEED supports the poorest, most vulnerable and marginalized communities and individuals in the target groups\r\nwhere we work.','About us','','inherit','closed','open','','372-revision-v1','','','2014-11-06 04:42:25','2014-11-06 04:42:25','',372,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=424',0,'revision','',0),(425,1,'2014-11-06 04:43:02','2014-11-06 04:43:02','<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">WHO WE ARE</span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Centre for Community Socio-economic and Environmental Development (CSEED) is a\r\nVietnamese Non - Governmental Organization (NGO), which was established by the Vietnam\r\nUnion of Science and Technology Associations (VUSTA) under Decision No 77/QD-LHH dated 17\r\nJanuary 2006. CSEED was formed by the staff of Community Development Department of CIDSE\r\nVietnam - an International NGO - as a part of the planned empowerment and management role\r\nhand-over to a local NGO after CIDSE\'s 27 years of working in Vietnam.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">CSEED staff who had worked with International NGOs have good knowledge and skills in\r\nmanaging programme. Our professional expertise in economics, agriculture, sociology and\r\nenvironment are relevant to the organization\'s programme focus.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Our Vision</span></h4>\r\nVulnerable and marginalized communities are empowered within equitable society and achieve\r\nsustainable livelihoods and environmental development.\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Our Mission</span></h4>\r\nCSEED enables vulnerable and marginalized communities to achieve sustainable livelihoods and\r\nenvironmental development through:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Supporting communities and partner organisations to initiate and manage livelihoods and\r\nenvironmental development programme