e sources for the farmers and therefore, reduce their vulnerability to few main\ncrops, and to risks in nature and society.</li>\n	<li>Participatory approach in combination with grassroots democracy promotion to create active\nresponses from the local people in development from planning, implementing, monitoring,\nevaluation and reporting of their local development plans at village and commune level;</li>\n	<li>Farmer-to-farmer approach to strengthen capacity of key farmers who will work as nuclear\nreaction agents for spreading technical production and management knowledge and improving\nrelated skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">DEVELOPMENT FOCUS</span></h4>\nThe CSEED programme focuses on livelihoods and environment.\n<h5><span style=\"color: #008000;\"> In livelihoods, CSEED focuses on 3 main sectors:</span></h5>\n<ol>\n	<li>Agriculture/Food sovereignty</li>\n	<li>Non-farm production</li>\n	<li>Forestry</li>\n</ol>\n<h5><span style=\"color: #008000;\"> In environment, we focus on:</span></h5>\n<ul>\n	<li>Disaster preparedness, climate change adaptation and mitigation initiatives (eg. reforestation, develop community capacity to cope with negative effects of environmental degradation, etc.)Sanitation education</li>\n</ul>\n<h5><span style=\"color: #008000;\"> Social and environmental cross-cutting issues integrated in the livelihoods and</span>\n<span style=\"color: #008000;\"> environmental programmes/projects:</span></h5>\n- Gender equity\n- Promotion of people\'s and community\'s participation in development process\n- Capacity building and development of Community-based Organisations (CBOs)\n- Environment protection (environmental issues will be tacked by preventive protective actions and\naddressing the degradation that has already occured in these communities).','OUR PROGRAMME','','inherit','closed','open','','223-autosave-v1','','','2014-11-07 03:42:46','2014-11-07 03:42:46','',223,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=435',0,'revision','',0)