ned objective, project will support to address main constraints suffered by\r\nvillagers in 4 surveyed villages, ie. food shortage, poor living condition, insufficient service, inadequate\r\ninclusion of poor ethnic minority communities and discrimination against women. Strategies to address\r\nthese constraints are:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','GREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN TAN SON DISTRICT, PHU  THO PROVINCE – (Project code: VC017)','','inherit','closed','open','','33-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 04:24:44','2014-11-07 04:24:44','',33,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=452',0,'revision','',0),(453,1,'2014-11-07 04:27:18','2014-11-07 04:27:18','On 05th of April 2013, Tan Son District People\'s Committee (DPC), Phu Tho province and Centre for Community Socio-Economic and Environmental Development – CSEED signed agreement for project \"Improving quality of life for rural poor\".\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_0720.jpg\" alt=\"meeting\" width=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis project is finaned by European Union in Vietnam and Entraide et Fraternite in Belgium. The project will be implemented in Thu Cuc and Vinh Tien commune, Tan Son district, Phu Tho province. Project duration is 3 years from March 2013 to February 2016. Project specific objective is to imoprove income, living condition and quality of life of poor ethinic minority families and their participation in development process.\r\n\r\nTo achieve above mentioned objective, project will support to address main constraints suffered by villagers in 4 surveyed villages, ie. food shortage, poor living condition, insufficient service, inadequate inclusion of poor ethnic minority communities and discrimination against women. Strategies to address these constraints are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Capacity building for local authorities, technical staff at district and commune level and\r\ncommunity-based organisation so that they can support communities implementing the action\r\neffectively and manage development process beyond this project;</li>\r\n	<li>Capacity building for villagers on participatory planning, participation in decision making, technical\r\nproduction and bussiness for current crops/animal raising and piloting new crops to improve\r\nincome and food security.</li>\r\n	<li>Provision of in-kind support and construction of irrigation system for improving agriculture\r\nproduction</li>\r\n	<li>Extending irrigation system into drinking water system by installing purifying system and\r\ncombining the technical training for environment friendly livelihoods extending its content into\r\nhygiene environment education for improved living condition of the villagers;</li>\r\n	<li>Advocating to local authority for improved extension and veterinary service system, effective\r\ninclusion of poor ethnic minority communities and of hard-to-reach villages in development\r\nprocess which will provide opportunities to poor ethnic minority people to take part in all forms of\r\nparticipation including participating in planning, implementing, benefiting and decision making.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','GREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN TAN SON DISTRICT, PHU  THO PROVINCE – (Project code: VC017)','','inherit','closed','open','','33-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 04:27:18','2014-11-07 04:27:18','',33,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=453',0,'revision','',0),(454,1,'2014-11-07 04:27:36','2014-11-07 04:27:36','On 05th of April 2013, Tan Son District People\'s Committee (DPC), Phu Tho province and Centre for Community Socio-Economic and Environmental Development – CSEED signed agreement for project \"Improving quality of life for rural poor\".\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_0720.jpg\" alt=\"meeting\" width=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis project is finaned by European Union in Vietnam and Entraide et Fraternite in Belgium. The project will be implemented in Thu Cuc and Vinh Tien commune, Tan Son district, Phu Tho province. Project duration is 3 years from March 2013 to February 2016. Project specific objective is to imoprove income, living condition and quality of life of poor ethinic minority families and their participation in development process.\r\n\r\nTo achieve above mentioned objective, project will support to address main constraints suffered by villagers in 4 surveyed villages, ie. food shortage, poor living condition, insufficient service, inadequate inclusion of poor ethnic minority communities and discrimination against women. Strategies to address these constraints are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Capacity building for local authorities, technical staff at district and commune level and\r\ncommunity-based organisation so that they can support communities implementing the action\r\neffectively and manage development process beyond this project;</li>\r\n	<li>Capacity building for villagers on participatory planning, participation in decision making, technical\r\nproduction and bussiness for current crops/animal raising and piloting new crops to improve\r\nincome and food security.</li>\r\n	<li>Provision of in-kind support and construction of irrigation system for improving agriculture\r\nproduction</li>\r\n	<li>Extending irrigation system into drinking water system by installing purifying system and\r\ncombining the technical training for environment friendly livelihoods extending its content into\r\nhygiene environment education for improved living condition of the villagers;</li>\r\n	<li>Advocating to local authority for improved extension and veterinary service system, effective\r\ninclusion of poor ethnic minority communities and of hard-to-reach villages in development\r\nprocess which will provide opportunities to poor ethnic minority people to take part in all forms of\r\nparticipation including participating in planning, implementing, benefiting and decision making.</li>\r\n</ul>','GREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN TAN SON DISTRICT, PHU  THO PROVINCE – (Project code: VC017)','','inherit','closed','open','','33-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 04:27:36','2014-11-07 04:27:36','',33,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=454',0,'revision','',0),(455,1,'2014-11-07 04:30:19','2014-11-07 04:30:19','On 09th of February 2012, Tan Son District People\'s Committee (DPC), Phu Tho province and Centre for Community Socio-Economic and Environmental Development – CSEED signed agreement for project \"Sustainable agro-forestry development and marketing of ecological products from poor rural families in Tan Son - Tan Son District, Phu Tho Province\n\nThe project is co-financed by Spanish Agency for International Development Cooperation - AECID and a Spanish NGO - CONEMUND. The project will be implemented in four poor villages of Dong Son and My Thuan communes, Tan Son district, Phu Tho province.\n\nAccording the project agreement, the project will be implemented within 2-year time with the aim to improve food security through improved agricultural and forestry livelihoods for poor people in four villages of two communes in Tan Son district, Phu Tho province.\n\nSpeaking at the signing ceremony, Mr Bui Van Huan, Vice Chair of Tan Son District People’s Committee, Chairman of Project Management Board said that this project in a poor district of Tan Son is not only a great opportunity to improve people\'s lives through the development of sustainable livelihoods, but it also helps improving capacity of officials at various levels in implementing project activities and using new skills in performing their organisations’\nmandates. Tan Son District People’s Committee will assign relevant and committed staff to implement project\neffectively.','AGREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN TAN SON DISTRICT, PHU  THO PROVINCE– VC015','','inherit','closed','open','','48-autosave-v1','','','2014-11-07 04:30:19','2014-11-07 04:30:19','',48,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=455',0,'revision','',0),(456,1,'2014-11-07 04:30:38','2014-11-07 04:30:38','On 09th of February 2012, Tan Son District People\'s Committee (DPC), Phu Tho province and Centre for Community Socio-Economic and Environmental Development – CSEED signed agreement for project \"Sustainable agro-forestry development and marketing of ecological products from poor rural families in Tan Son - Tan Son District, Phu Tho Province\r\n\r\nThe project is co-financed by Spanish Agency for International Development Cooperation - AECID and a Spanish NGO - CONEMUND. The project will be implemented in four poor villages of Dong Son and My Thuan communes, Tan Son district, Phu Tho province.\r\n\r\nAccording the project agreement, the project will be implemented within 2-year time with the aim to improve food security through improved agricultural and forestry livelihoods for poor people in four villages of two communes in Tan Son district, Phu Tho province.\r\n\r\nSpeaking at the signing ceremony, Mr Bui Van Huan, Vice Chair of Tan Son District People’s Committee, Chairman of Project Management Board said that this project in a poor district of Tan Son is not only a great opportunity to improve people\'s lives through the development of sustainable livelihoods, but it also helps improving capacity of officials at various levels in implementing project activities and using new skills in performing their organisations’ mandates. Tan Son District People’s Committee will assign relevant and committed staff to implement project effectively.','AGREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN TAN SON DISTRICT, PHU  THO PROVINCE– VC015','','inherit','closed','open','','48-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 04:30:38','2014-11-07 04:30:38','',48,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=456',0,'revision','',0),(457,1,'2014-11-07 04:36:51','2014-11-07 04:36:51','On 12 January 2011, the Project Agreement Signing Ceremony was held formally at Thai Thuy District People\'s Committee between CSEED and Thai Thuy District – Thai Binh Province.\n\n\n[one_half]&nbsp;<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1107.jpg\" alt=\"image45_1\" />[/one_half]\n\n[one_half_last][/one_half_last]\n\n\nThe project “Diversified livelihoods and improved resilience of the vulnerable coastal communities toward climate change adaptation in Thai Thuy District, Thai Binh Province” (Project Code: VC011) is supported by Misereor and will be implemented from October 2010 until September 2013.\n\nThe main purpose of this project is to reduce vulnerability of the coastal communities in five villages of Thai Do and Thai Thuong communes through diversifying their livelihoods and building up their resilience towards climate change adaptation in sustainable manner. The project is expected to bring direct benefits to 5,048 people belong to 1,206 households of 5 villages in Thai Do and Thai Thuong communes, Thai Thuy District, Thai Binh Province. Most of project beneficiaries will be farmers engaging in agriculture and aquaculture production and pupils who have suffered and will climate change and environment issues in the coming years. The poor will be prioritized because of their low response capacity and high vulnerability to the climate changes. The project will focus on some following main matters:\n<ul>\n	<li>Diversifying the sustainable aquaculture;</li>\n	<li>Developing the good model of sustainable productions adapting with climate change and meeting the food security</li>\n	<li>Improving the community’s capacity on climate change preventation</li>\n</ul>','AGREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN THAI BINH PROVINCE – VC011','','inherit','closed','open','','45-autosave-v1','','','2014-11-07 04:36:51','2014-11-07 04:36:51','',45,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=457',0,'revision','',0),(458,1,'2014-11-07 04:37:09','2014-11-07 04:37:09','On 12 January 2011, the Project Agreement Signing Ceremony was held formally at Thai Thuy District People\'s Committee between CSEED and Thai Thuy District – Thai Binh Province.\r\n\r\n\r\n[one_half]&nbsp;<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1107.jp