t – Thai Binh Province.\r\n\r\n\r\n[one_half]<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1107.jpg\" alt=\"image45_1\" width=\"300px\"/>[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1113.jpg\" alt=\"img45_2\" width= \"300px\" />[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\n\r\nThe project “Diversified livelihoods and improved resilience of the vulnerable coastal communities toward climate change adaptation in Thai Thuy District, Thai Binh Province” (Project Code: VC011) is supported by Misereor and will be implemented from October 2010 until September 2013.\r\n\r\nThe main purpose of this project is to reduce vulnerability of the coastal communities in five villages of Thai Do and Thai Thuong communes through diversifying their livelihoods and building up their resilience towards climate change adaptation in sustainable manner. The project is expected to bring direct benefits to 5,048 people belong to 1,206 households of 5 villages in Thai Do and Thai Thuong communes, Thai Thuy District, Thai Binh Province. Most of project beneficiaries will be farmers engaging in agriculture and aquaculture production and pupils who have suffered and will climate change and environment issues in the coming years. The poor will be prioritized because of their low response capacity and high vulnerability to the climate changes. The project will focus on some following main matters:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Diversifying the sustainable aquaculture;</li>\r\n	<li>Developing the good model of sustainable productions adapting with climate change and meeting the food security</li>\r\n	<li>Improving the community’s capacity on climate change preventation</li>\r\n</ul>','AGREEMENT SIGNING FOR NEW PROJECT IN THAI BINH PROVINCE – VC011','','inherit','closed','open','','45-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 04:38:03','2014-11-07 04:38:03','',45,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=459',0,'revision','',0),(460,1,'2014-11-07 04:41:26','2014-11-07 04:41:26','[one_half]<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1266.jpg\" alt=\"image30_1\" width=\"300px\" />[/one_half]\n\n[one_half_last]\nKhuoi Deng I and II villages are two villages of Tan Son commune, Cho Moi district,Bac Kan province having natural bamboo area up to 180 ha.\nThese bamboo resources have partially contributed to villager’s income here. However, the local bamboo was just sold as raw products such as cutting tree and binding them to sell at low price.\n[/one_half_last]\n\nUnder Cho Moi Integrated Community Development Project, In August 2009, CSEED in collaboration with Xuan Lai traditional bamboo processing co-operative organized basic and advanced training courses and exposure visit for villagers of these two villages to production site of Xuan Lai co-operative. A set of bamboo processing machine was also provided to the two villages. After receiving the above-mentioned supports, villagers were able to do preliminary processing i.e. they know how to make the tree from curve\nto straight and to make the most of the tree; therefore 30% material was saved. This contributed to sustain bamboo for future usage.In addition, the products are very aesthetic, eye-catched and it can adapt household’s needs such as table, chair, tea tray, fishing-rod, farmer’s pipe...','Effects from CSEED support to bamboo furniture processing in  Cho Moi Integrated Community Development Project','','inherit','closed','open','','30-autosave-v1','','','2014-11-07 04:41:26','2014-11-07 04:41:26','',30,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=460',0,'revision','',0),(461,1,'2014-11-07 04:40:23','2014-11-07 04:40:23','\r\n[one_half]<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1266.jpg\" alt=\"image30_1\" width=\"300px\"/>[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]\r\nKhuoi Deng I and II villages are two villages of Tan Son commune, Cho Moi district,Bac Kan province having natural bamboo area up to 180 ha.\r\nThese bamboo resources have partially contributed to villager’s income here. However, the local bamboo was just sold as raw products such as cutting tree and binding them to sell at low price.\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\n \r\n','Effects from CSEED support to bamboo furniture processing in  Cho Moi Integrated Community Development Project','','inherit','closed','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 04:40:23','2014-11-07 04:40:23','',30,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=461',0,'revision','',0),(462,1,'2014-11-07 04:42:49','2014-11-07 04:42:49','[one_half]<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1266.jpg\" alt=\"image30_1\" width=\"300px\" />[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]\r\nKhuoi Deng I and II villages are two villages of Tan Son commune, Cho Moi district,Bac Kan province having natural bamboo area up to 180 ha.\r\nThese bamboo resources have partially contributed to villager’s income here. However, the local bamboo was just sold as raw products such as cutting tree and binding them to sell at low price.\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\nUnder Cho Moi Integrated Community Development Project, In August 2009, CSEED in collaboration with Xuan Lai traditional bamboo processing co-operative organized basic and advanced training courses and exposure visit for villagers of these two villages to production site of Xuan Lai co-operative. A set of bamboo processing machine was also provided to the two villages. After receiving the above-mentioned supports, villagers were able to do preliminary processing i.e. they know how to make the tree from curve\r\nto straight and to make the most of the tree; therefore 30% material was saved. This contributed to sustain bamboo for future usage.In addition, the products are very aesthetic, eye-catched and it can adapt household’s needs such as table, chair, tea tray, fishing-rod, farmer’s pipe...\r\n\r\n&nbsp;<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Cay-mot-danh.jpg\" alt=\"img30_2\" width=\"600px\"/>\r\n\r\nMoreover, Xuan Lai traditional bamboo processing co-operative also expressed their demand to buy the big quantity of preliminarily processed bamboo with about two times higher price than current price. Some villagers and dealers also expressed their interests in buying these products at 3-5 times higher price than selling raw materials.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn conclusion, those support is a good start which enable villagers in two villages identify their valuable local resources and have good plan for using these resources for their development.. In the coming time, CSEED will support to enable them to work as bamboo processing group and to follow environmental friendly manner systematically. Thus, we hope this activity can contribute to bring effects and sustainability in socio-economic developments for households in these two villages.','Effects from CSEED support to bamboo furniture processing in  Cho Moi Integrated Community Development Project','','inherit','closed','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 04:42:49','2014-11-07 04:42:49','',30,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=462',0,'revision','',0),(463,1,'2014-11-07 04:43:09','2014-11-07 04:43:09','[one_half]<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_1266.jpg\" alt=\"image30_1\" width=\"300px\" />[/one_half]\r\n\r\n[one_half_last]\r\nKhuoi Deng I and II villages are two villages of Tan Son commune, Cho Moi district,Bac Kan province having natural bamboo area up to 180 ha.\r\nThese bamboo resources have partially contributed to villager’s income here. However, the local bamboo was just sold as raw products such as cutting tree and binding them to sell at low price.\r\n[/one_half_last]\r\n\r\nUnder Cho Moi Integrated Community Development Project, In August 2009, CSEED in collaboration with Xuan Lai traditional bamboo processing co-operative organized basic and advanced training courses and exposure visit for villagers of these two villages to production site of Xuan Lai co-operative. A set of bamboo processing machin