 sixty participants attented the workshop were CSEED Director and Project Officer, Project Management Board and Working Team, representatives of project related Departments of Luong Son district and beneficiaries. After the speech summarily reported all project activities, the participants actively contributed their opinions to the project, both on successes and obstacles/limitations. The project were highly appreciated with good impacts to increase the households’ income through loan, breeding animals, contribute to improve the villagers’ health, enthusiasm of stakeholders, good performance of project management board members,…\n\nMr. Ly Kim Huong, Dao ethnic monirity, Ngoc Lam village, Cao Ram commune, said: “We had no concept of gender equality until the project comes to training. We, the men often took rests after working on the field, just gathered and talked together, we ignored the women’s voice as we thought that women knew nothing. But, since CIDSE/CSEED training on gender equality, men in our village has helped their wives much more, and discuss with the wives in any issues”.\n\nMoreover, literacy training was one of the most expected activities to the people here. Inspite of the rain, the coldness, the busyness, they still go to class with a torch every evening.\n\nBesides, there were still some limitations such as some project activities have not met the villagers’ needs like few literacy classes, project supported training on animal raising and provided with breedings but lack of veterinary training. The lessons-learnt were consolidated for a better performance in the future\n\nThe local authorities and Vulunteer Village Development Committee in each village were committed to continue managing and implementing the project activities. They also assigned the responsibilities to each stakeholders clearly and drew the mechanism of project managing and reporting.\n\nAll the project stakeholders, especially the beneficiaries, expected that the project will continue following phases. In which, handmade paper production still needs more supports.\n\nThis is considered one of the most sucessful CSEED’s projects.','Closing Workshop of VC004 project in Luong Son District – Hoa Binh  Province','','inherit','closed','open','','21-autosave-v1','','','2014-11-07 08:51:01','2014-11-07 08:51:01','',21,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=472',0,'revision','',0),(473,1,'2014-11-07 08:51:25','2014-11-07 08:51:25','On 29 April 2009, the closing workshop of VC004 project Community Asset Improvement for Livelihoods of Poor Communities was held in Luong Son People’s Committee.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/02banner.jpg.jpg\" alt=\"img21\" />\r\n\r\nMore than sixty participants attented the workshop were CSEED Director and Project Officer, Project Management Board and Working Team, representatives of project related Departments of Luong Son district and beneficiaries. After the speech summarily reported all project activities, the participants actively contributed their opinions to the project, both on successes and obstacles/limitations. The project were highly appreciated with good impacts to increase the households’ income through loan, breeding animals, contribute to improve the villagers’ health, enthusiasm of stakeholders, good performance of project management board members,…\r\n\r\nMr. Ly Kim Huong, Dao ethnic monirity, Ngoc Lam village, Cao Ram commune, said: “We had no concept of gender equality until the project comes to training. We, the men often took rests after working on the field, just gathered and talked together, we ignored the women’s voice as we thought that women knew nothing. But, since CIDSE/CSEED training on gender equality, men in our village has helped their wives much more, and discuss with the wives in any issues”.\r\n\r\nMoreover, literacy training was one of the most expected activities to the people here. Inspite of the rain, the coldness, the busyness, they still go to cl