 of the two poorest communes in Van Quan: Phu My and Viet Yen and target in livelihoods and environmental protection with cross-cutting issues like gender equality, community-based organnisation capacity building.','NEW PROJECT AGREEMENT SIGNED FOR LANG SON PROVINCE','','inherit','closed','open','','39-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 08:54:29','2014-11-07 08:54:29','',39,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=478',0,'revision','',0),(479,1,'2014-11-07 08:56:08','2014-11-07 08:56:08','Yesterday, Sunday 15 February 2009, in vestige Van Mieu - Quoc Tu Giam, CSEED held-up an Exhibition on Giấy Dó (Handmade paper) under the CSEED project VC004 funded by Cordaid - Neitherlands. \n\nAttending the exhibition, the visitors had served with cơm-lam (bamboo-tube rice) and witnessed the processes of handmade paper production and products from Giấy Dó such as envelops, greeting cards, album, calendar,… . \n\nThe Muong ethnic minority group in Suoi Co village, Hop Hoa commune, Luong Son district, Hoa Binh province is the target group of this project component. They lived on agriculture production before, but now their incomes and living conditions have been improved thanks party to handmade paper production. CSEED\'s VC004 project has supported\nthe Suoi Co group with the provision of several initial facilities and equipment, co-operated with HRPC in technical training, material reservation as well as business and management capacity building. \n\nThe CSEED model of Giấy Dó production has made both social and economic impacts. It initially brought abouteconomic benefit for the group, with each member household having increased their monthly income by VND 500,000 (equivalent to USD 30) . Moreover, the use of this model has contributed to the preservation of some of the indigenous knowledge of the Vietnamese people, and has made a small contribution to the cause of poverty reduction in the country. ','CSEED holds a Giấy Dó (Handmade paper)Exhibition','','inherit','closed','open','','7-autosave-v1','','','2014-11-07 08:56:08','2014-11-07 08:56:08','',7,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=479',0,'revision','',0),(480,1,'2014-11-07 08:56:42','2014-11-07 08:56:42','<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/02banner.jpg.jpg\" alt=\"img7\" width=\"600px\"/>\r\n\r\nYesterday, Sunday 15 February 2009, in vestige Van Mieu - Quoc Tu Giam, CSEED held-up an Exhibition on Giấy Dó (Handmade paper) under the CSEED project VC004 funded by Cordaid - Neitherlands. \r\n\r\nAttending the exhibition, the visitors had served with cơm-lam (bamboo-tube rice) and witnessed the processes of handmade paper production and products from Giấy Dó such as envelops, greeting cards, album, calendar,… . \r\n\r\nThe Muong ethnic minority group in Suoi Co village, Hop Hoa commune, Luong Son district, Hoa Binh province is the target group of this project component. They lived on agriculture production before, but now their incomes and living conditions have been improved thanks party to handmade paper production. CSEED\'s VC004 project has supported\r\nthe Suoi Co group with the provision of several initial facilities and equipment, co-operated with HRPC in technical training, material reservation as well as business and management capacity building. \r\n\r\nThe CSEED model of Giấy Dó production has made both social and economic impacts. It initially brought abouteconomic benefit for the group, with each member household having increased their monthly income by VND 500,000 (equivalent to USD 30) . Moreover, the use of this model has contributed to the preservation of some of the indigenous knowledge of the Vietnamese people, and has made a small contribution to the cause of poverty reduction in the country. ','CSEED holds a Giấy Dó (Handmade paper)Exhibition','','inherit','closed','open','','7-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 08:56:42','2014-11-07 08:56:42','',7,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=480',0,'revision','',0),(481,1,'2014-11-07 08:57:57','2014-11-07 08:57:57','Dear colleagues and friends,\r\n \r\nNon-farm is one of the activities supporting the disadvantaged and vulnerable communities to improve \r\ntheir livelihoods. As a result of this support, CSEED organises an exhibition on Giay Do (handmade \r\npaper) production performed by the villagers in Suoi Co village, Hop Hoa commune, Hoa Binh province - \r\none of CSEED VC004 project beneficiaries.\r\n \r\nTime: 9am - 5 pm, Sunday 15 February 2009\r\nVenue: Van Mieu - Quoc Tu Giam, Hanoi\r\n \r\nCSEED would like to invite you to this event.\r\n \r\nCSEED hopes to receive your support and attendance to this event as your encouragement to the \r\ndisavantaged and vulnerable communities. \r\n \r\nPlease download the letter of invitation and the agend','Invitation to CSEED Handmade Paper Exhibition','','inherit','closed','open','','36-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 08:57:57','2014-11-07 08:57:57','',36,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=481',0,'revision','',0),(482,1,'2014-11-07 09:52:26','2014-11-07 09:52:26','','image4_2','','inherit','closed','open','','image4_2','','','2014-11-07 09:52:26','2014-11-07 09:52:26','',0,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/image4_2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(483,1,'2014-11-07 09:52:48','2014-11-07 09:52:48','','image4_1','','inherit','closed','open','','image4_1','','','2014-11-07 09:52:48','2014-11-07 09:52:48','',0,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/image4_1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(484,1,'2014-11-07 09:53:43','2014-11-07 09:53:43','During 26 and 28 December 2008, the handing over ceremony of irrigation and clean-water constructions between CSEED and Huu Lung District People\'s Committee, Lang Son province was organised under the project VC006 funded by Manos Unidas (Spain). \n\nThe irrigation and clean-water constructions including two irrigation schemes of O O and Ho Rung Chua  and two clean-water system were completed which improve the accessibility to drinking and irrigation water for the villagers here. Specially, 1,317 people of Dong Sinh, Dong Ma, Da Mai and Tan Hop villages - Tan Lap commune have got benefits from the upgraded irrigation schemes as they have their paddy fields within the irrigated area and 252 people of Lan Mo and Lan Vau villages have received the supports from the project for households-scale water tanks to store clean water for daily use as these two villages are suffering from lack of clean water as the water resources from forest mountain become less.\n\nThe villagers here are very happy to receive the water and they are all committed to strictly follow the regulations of water use and project maintainance. As estimated, spring crop for rice will be got 40 ha more in O O system and 25ha more in Ho Rung Chua; winter crop for rice will be got 45 ha more in O O system and 25 ha more in Ho Rung Chua system for maize, soybean, potato, vegetables... Rice yields increased from 4 tons/ha - 4.2 tons/ha for summer crop 3.5 tons/ha - 3.8 tons/ha for spring crop. Estimated a total net income generated is around VND 694,175,000 per year equivalent to USD 43,659.     ','Handing-over ceremony of irrigation and clean-water constructions between CSEED and Huu Lung District - Lang Son province','','inherit','closed','open','','4-autosave-v1','','','2014-11-07 09:53:43','2014-11-07 09:53:43','',4,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=484',0,'revision','',0),(485,1,'2014-11-07 09:54:04','2014-11-07 09:54:04','<img src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/image4_1.jpg\" alt=\"img4\" width=\"500px\" />\r\n\r\nDuring 26 and 28 December 2008, the handing over ceremony of irrigation and clean-water constructions between CSEED and Huu Lung District People\'s Committee, Lang Son province was organised under the project VC006 funded by Manos Unidas (Spain). \r\n\r\nThe irrigation and clean-water constructions including two irrigation schemes of O O and Ho Rung Chua  and two clean-water system were completed which improve the accessibility to drinking and irrigation water for the villagers here. Specially, 1,317 people of Dong Sinh, Dong Ma, Da Mai and Tan Hop villages - Tan Lap commune have got benefits from the upgraded irrigation schemes as they have their paddy fields within the irrigated area and 252 people of Lan Mo and Lan Vau villages have received the supports from the project for households-scale water tanks to store clean water for daily use as these two villages are suffering from lack of clean water as the water resources from forest mountain become less.\r\n\r\nThe villagers here are very happy to receive the water and they are all committed to strictly follow the regulations of water use and project maintainance. As estimated, spring crop for rice will be got 40 ha more in O O system and 25ha more in Ho Rung Chua; winter crop for rice will be got 45 ha more in O O system and 25 ha more in Ho Rung Chua system for maize, soybean, potato, vegetables... Rice yields increased from 4 tons/ha - 4.2 tons/ha for summer crop 3.5 tons/ha - 3.8 tons/ha for spring crop. Estimated a total net income generated is around VND 694,175,000 per year equivalent to USD 43,659.     ','Handing-over ceremony of irrigation and clean-water constructions between CSEED and Huu Lung District - Lang Son province','','inherit','closed','open','','4-revision-v1','','','2014-11-07 09:54:04','2014-11-07 09:54:04','',4,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=485',0,'revision','',0),(486,1,'2014-11-11 02:51:12','2014-11-11 02:51:12','','banner CSEED','','inherit','closed','open','','banner-cseed','','','2014-11-11 03:30:55','2014-11-11 03:30:55','',0,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/banner-CSEED.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(487,1,'2014-11-11 02:51:38','2014-11-11 02:51:38','','banner CSEED','','inherit','closed','open','','banner-cseed-2','','','2014-11-11 02:51:38','2014-11-11 02:51:38','',0,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/banner-CSEED1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(493,1,'2014-11-17 09:04:39','2014-11-17 09:04:39','<h4><span style=\"color: #339966;\">CHUNG TÔI LÀ AI</span></h4>\r\nTrung tâm hộ nghị quốc giả về phồng chổng mộng\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trung tâm Phát triển Kinh tế-Xã hội và Môi trường Cộng đồng (CSEED), là một tổ chức phi chính phủ độc lập của Việt Nam, hoạt động phi lợi nhuận, được thành lập theo Quyết định số 77/QĐ-LHH ban ngày 17/1/2006 của Liên hiệp các Hội Khoa học và Kỹ thuật Việt Nam (VUSTA). Trung tâm CSEED được thành lập bởi các cán bộ, nhân viên trong Ban Phát triển Cộng đồng của CIDSE Việt Nam - Tổ chức Phi Chính Phủ Quốc Tế. Đây là một phần của quá trình nâng cao năng lực và chuyển giao vai trò quản lý chương trình cho tổ chức phi chính phủ Việt Nam sau 27 năm hoạt động trong lĩnh vực hỗ trợ phát triển của CIDSE Việt Nam.</p>\r\nCác nhân viên của Trung tâm CSEED là những cán bộ đã làm việc lâu năm và có kinh nghiệm quản lý các dự án phát triển trong các tổ chức Phi chính phủ quốc tế, được đào tạo về các lĩnh vực kinh tế, nông nghiệp, xã hội học và môi trường phù hợp với trọng tâm chương trình của tổ chức.\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #339966;\">Tầm Nhìn</span><strong> </strong></h4>\r\nCộng đồng nghèo và bị thiệt thòi nâng cao năng lực và vị trí của mình trong một xã hội công bằng và đạt được sự phát triển bền vững thông qua các chương trình phát triển sinh kế và bảo vệ môi trường.\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #339966;\">Sứ Mệnh </span></h4>\r\nCSEED hỗ trợ cho cộng đồng nghèo và bị thiệt thòi phát triển năng lực để có thể quản lý các chương trình sinh kế và bảo vệ môi trường bền vững thông qua:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hỗ trợ cộng đồng và đối tác trong việc xây dựng và quản lý các chương trình, dự án phát triển sinh kế và bảo vệ môi trường;</li>\r\n	<li>Củng cố năng lực người dân và của các tổ chức tại cộng đồng và sự tiếp cận của họ tới nguồn lực;</li>\r\n	<li>Triển khai thí điểm các sáng kiến, mô hình phát triển và thực hiện nghiên cứu hành động;</li>\r\n	<li>Tham gia vận động với các chính sách phát triển sinh kế và môi trường và việc thực hiện các chính sách đó.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #339966;\">Giá Trị</span></h4>\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-49\" title=\"6813233319_752a42a794_b\" src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_0720.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"240\" height=\"150\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tự chủ</li>\r\n	<li>Hợp tác</li>\r\n	<li>Công bằng</li>\r\n	<li>Minh bạch và trách nhiệm</li>\r\n	<li>Hiệu quả</li>\r\n	<li>Bền vững</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #339966;\">Nhóm Đối Tượng Mục Tiêu</span></h4>\r\nCSEED tập trung hỗ trợ cho các cộng đồng nghèo và bị thiệt thòi, đặc biệt là hỗ trợ những người nghèo nhất, dễ bị tổn thương và thiệt thòi nhất ở các cộng đồng này.','GIỚI THIỆU','','publish','closed','open','','gioi-thieu','','','2014-11-17 16:45:00','2014-11-17 16:45:00','',0,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?page_id=493',0,'page','',0),(494,1,'2014-11-17 09:00:22','2014-11-17 09:00:22','<a href=\"http://www.cseed.org.vn/viewer.asp?pgid=10&amp;aid=57\"><span style=\"color: #3c9b1b;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>Chúng tôi là ai</b></span></span></span></a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trung tâm Phát triển Kinh tế-Xã hội và Môi trường Cộng đồng (CSEED), là một tổ chức phi chính phủ độc lập của Việt Nam, hoạt động phi lợi nhuận, được thành lập theo Quyết định số 77/QĐ-LHH ban ngày 17/1/2006 của Liên hiệp các Hội Khoa học và Kỹ thuật Việt Nam (VUSTA). Trung tâm CSEED được thành lập bởi các cán bộ, nhân viên trong Ban Phát triển Cộng đồng của CIDSE Việt Nam - Tổ chức Phi Chính Phủ Quốc Tế. Đây là một phần của quá trình nâng cao năng lực và chuyển giao vai trò quản lý chương trình cho tổ chức phi chính phủ Việt Nam sau 27 năm hoạt động trong lĩnh vực hỗ trợ phát triển của CIDSE Việt Nam.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Our Vision</span></h4>\r\nVulnerable and marginalized communities are empowered within equitable society and achieve\r\nsustainable livelihoods and environmental development.\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Our Mission</span></h4>\r\nCSEED enables vulnerable and marginalized communities to achieve sustainable livelihoods and\r\nenvironmental development through:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Supporting communities and partner organisations to initiate and manage livelihoods and\r\nenvironmental development programmes</li>\r\n	<li>Strengthening capacities of communities and farmers’ groups and their access to resources</li>\r\n	<li>Piloting innovative development initiatives and conducting action research</li>\r\n	<li>Advocating on livelihoods and environmental policies and implementation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Our Values</span></h4>\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-49\" title=\"6813233319_752a42a794_b\" src=\"http://cseed.justvelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/IMG_0720.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"240\" height=\"150\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ownership</li>\r\n	<li>Partnership</li>\r\n	<li>Equity</li>\r\n	<li>Transparency and Accountability</li>\r\n	<li>Efficiency</li>\r\n	<li>Sustainability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Target Groups</span></h4>\r\nCSEED supports the poorest, most vulnerable and marginalized communities and individuals in the target groups\r\nwhere we work.','GIỚI THIỆU','','inherit','closed','open','','493-revision-v1','','','2014-11-17 09:00:22','2014-11-17 09:00:22','',493,'http://cseed.justvelo.com/?p=494',0,'revision','',0),(495,1,'2014-11-17 09:04:39','2014-11-17 09:04:39','<a href=\"http://www.cseed.org.vn/viewer.asp?pgid=10&amp;aid=57\"><span style=\"color: #3c9b1b;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>Chúng tôi là ai</b></span></span></span></a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Trung tâm Phát triển Kinh tế-Xã hội và Môi trường Cộng đồng (CSEED), là một t